      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── PHASE 2: FILTER ─── -->
  <div class="section-divider">
    <div class="section-divider-line"></div>
    <div class="section-divider-label">Phase 2 — Create the JQL Filter (do this before adding gadgets)</div>
    <div class="section-divider-line"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 4 -->
  <div class="step-card">
    <div class="step-card-header">
      <div class="step-num-wrap">
        <div class="step-num phase-filter">4</div>
        <div class="step-connector"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card-title-area">
        <div class="step-phase-tag tag-filter">JQL Filter</div>
        <div class="step-card-title">Create and save your JQL filter — the backbone of this dashboard</div>
        <div class="step-card-subtitle">All gadgets will use this one saved filter. Get this right first before adding any gadgets.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card-body">

      <div class="action">
        <div class="action-icon-wrap ai-purple">🔍</div>
        <div class="action-content">
          <div class="action-label">What is a JQL filter?</div>
          <div class="action-text">JQL (Jira Query Language) is like a search formula. You write a condition — like "show me all SFTS issues raised by our team" — and Jira returns only those matching issues. A <strong>Saved Filter</strong> stores that formula with a name so you can reuse it across gadgets without rewriting it each time.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="action">
        <div class="action-icon-wrap ai-purple">🗂</div>
        <div class="action-content">
          <div class="action-label">Navigate to: Issues → Manage Filters</div>
          <div class="action-text">In the top nav, click <strong>"Filters"</strong> → then click <strong>"View all filters"</strong> → then click the <strong>"Create filter"</strong> button on that page. Alternatively go to <strong>Issues → Manage Filters → Create new filter</strong>.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="action">
        <div class="action-icon-wrap ai-purple">⌨️</div>
        <div class="action-content">
          <div class="action-label">Paste this JQL into the search bar</div>
          <div class="action-text">In the JQL text area (switch to Advanced mode if needed), paste this query. Replace the member names and group name with your actual values:</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="jql-block">
        <span class="jql-key">project</span> <span class="jql-op">in</span> (<span class="jql-str">"EMOST"</span>, <span class="jql-str">"ESJD"</span>)<br>
        <span class="jql-op">AND</span> <span class="jql-key">labels</span> <span class="jql-op">=</span> <span class="jql-str">"SFTS"</span><br>
        <span class="jql-op">AND</span> <span class="jql-key">reporter</span> <span class="jql-op">in</span> (<span class="jql-str">"john.doe"</span>, <span class="jql-str">"jane.smith"</span>, <span class="jql-str">"ravi.kumar"</span>)<br>
        <span class="jql-op">AND</span> <span class="jql-key">assignee</span> <span class="jql-op">in</span> <span class="jql-op">membersOf</span>(<span class="jql-str">"emost-esjd-team"</span>)<br>
        <span class="jql-op">ORDER BY</span> <span class="jql-key">created</span> <span class="jql-op">DESC</span>
      </div>

      <div class="action">
        <div class="action-icon-wrap ai-purple">🔎</div>
        <div class="action-content">
          <div class="action-label">What each JQL line means</div>
          <div class="action-text">
            <strong>project in ("EMOST","ESJD")</strong> — Look inside only these two Jira projects where SFTS issues are raised.<br><br>
            <strong>labels = "SFTS"</strong> — Only fetch issues that are tagged with the label "SFTS" (this is how you scope only FTP-related stories).<br><br>
            <strong>reporter in (...)</strong> — Only stories that were <em>created/raised</em> by your team members. Replace with real Jira usernames.<br><br>
            <strong>assignee in membersOf(...)</strong> — Only stories that are <em>assigned to</em> the other team (EMOST/ESJD members). Replace with their team group name.<br><br>
            <strong>ORDER BY created DESC</strong> — Show the most recently raised issues at the top.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="action">
        <div class="action-icon-wrap ai-purple">💾</div>
        <div class="action-content">
          <div class="action-label">Save the filter with a clear name</div>
          <div class="action-text">Click <strong>"Save As"</strong> → In the name field type: <code>SFTS Team Raised Issues</code> → Under <strong>Permissions</strong>, set it to your team group → Click <strong>Save</strong>. You will now see this filter listed in your saved filters — remember the name, you'll need it in the next steps.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="warn-box">
        <span class="box-icon">⚠️</span>
        <div class="box-content"><strong>Important:</strong> If your SFTS issues don't use the label "SFTS", change <code>labels = "SFTS"</code> to whatever field your team uses — for example <code>component = "FTP"</code> or <code>customfield_10020 = "SFTS"</code>. Ask your Jira admin if unsure.</div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ─── PHASE 3: GADGETS ─── -->
  <div class="section-divider">
    <div class="section-divider-line"></div>
    <div class="section-divider-label">Phase 3 — Add &amp; Configure Gadgets on your Dashboard</div>
    <div class="section-divider-line"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 5 -->
  <div class="step-card">
    <div class="step-card-header">
      <div class="step-num-wrap">
        <div class="step-num phase-gadget">5</div>
        <div class="step-connector"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card-title-area">
        <div class="step-phase-tag tag-gadget">Gadgets</div>
        <div class="step-card-title">Go back to your dashboard and click "Add gadget"</div>
        <div class="step-card-subtitle">Gadgets are the individual panels/widgets on your dashboard. Each one shows a different view of your SFTS issues.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card-body">

      <div class="action">
        <div class="action-icon-wrap ai-teal">🔙</div>
        <div class="action-content">
          <div class="action-label">Navigate to your dashboard</div>
          <div class="action-text">Go to <strong>Dashboards → View all dashboards</strong> → find and click on <strong>"SFTS (FTP) Team Issue Tracker"</strong>. You will see an empty dashboard with 3 column placeholders and an <strong>"Add gadget"</strong> button in the top right.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="action">
        <div class="action-icon-wrap ai-teal">➕</div>
        <div class="action-content">
          <div class="action-label">What gadgets to add (and why)</div>
          <div class="action-text">Click <strong>"Add gadget"</strong> and search for each gadget by name. Add all 4 of these — each serves a specific purpose:</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="gadget-grid">
        <div class="gadget-card recommended">
          <div class="gadget-top">
            <div class="gadget-icon gi-blue">📊</div>
            <div class="gadget-name">Issue Statistics</div>
          </div>
          <span class="gadget-tag gt-must">Must add</span>
          <div class="gadget-desc">Shows a <strong>bar chart of story counts</strong> grouped by Reporter (who raised it) or Status. Add this twice — once for reporter count, once for status count.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gadget-card recommended">
          <div class="gadget-top">
            <div class="gadget-icon gi-teal">📋</div>
            <div class="gadget-name">Filter Results</div>
          </div>
          <span class="gadget-tag gt-must">Must add</span>
          <div class="gadget-desc">Shows a <strong>live scrollable table</strong> of all SFTS issues matching your filter — with columns like Summary, Status, Assignee, Priority.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gadget-card">
          <div class="gadget-top">
            <div class="gadget-icon gi-purple">📈</div>
            <div class="gadget-name">Created vs Resolved</div>
          </div>
          <span class="gadget-tag gt-good">Recommended</span>
          <div class="gadget-desc">Line chart showing <strong>how many SFTS issues are being raised vs resolved</strong> over time. Good for spotting backlogs building up.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="gadget-card">
          <div class="gadget-top">
            <div class="gadget-icon gi-amber">🔢</div>
            <div class="gadget-name">Two Dimensional Filter</div>
          </div>
          <span class="gadget-tag gt-good">Recommended</span>
          <div class="gadget-desc">A <strong>matrix table</strong> — rows = team members, columns = issue status. Shows exactly how many issues each person raised at each stage.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="info-box">
        <span class="box-icon">ℹ️</span>
        <div class="box-content">After each gadget is added to the dashboard, it will show an <strong>error or empty state</strong> until you configure it with your saved filter. That's normal — configuration is done in Steps 6–9 below.</div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 6 -->
  <div class="step-card">
    <div class="step-card-header">
      <div class="step-num-wrap">
        <div class="step-num phase-gadget">6</div>
        <div class="step-connector"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card-title-area">
        <div class="step-phase-tag tag-gadget">Configure</div>
        <div class="step-card-title">Configure "Issue Statistics" gadget — story count by team member</div>
        <div class="step-card-subtitle">This gadget answers: "How many SFTS issues has each team member raised?"</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-card-body">

      <div class="action">
        <div class="action-icon-wrap ai-teal">✏️</div>
        <div class="action-content">
          <div class="action-label">How to open the gadget settings</div>
          <div class="action-text">On the Issue Statistics gadget on your dashboard, look for the <strong>pencil icon ✏️ or three-dot menu (⋯)</strong> in the top right corner of that gadget. Click it and select <strong>"Edit"</strong>.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

